Sideskift

Side 2

Explanation

In this experiment you will be presented with 52 video clips, seen from a car's perspective. Colours, shapes and image quality will vary, but this should not influence the content and events in the clips. The example underneath shows how the same video may be represented in different ways, but still contains the same content or events.

You will only see one video clip at a time, and should give it one category that describes what happens in the video. Some categories might be used more frequently than others. When inquired about a clip's realism, please keep the following definition in mind:

"In the context of these videos, realism is thought of as how realistic the events are in comparison to real life events. This should not consider the quality of the images, but rather whether you think it's likely that the scenario or trajectory could happen in a real life trafic environment. A realistic video should also have a relatively continous flow, and stable transitions between consecutive images."
